Stress Reactions
Although academic stress due to family members during the COVID-19 lockdown
affected 41.1% of the respondents, irritability, arguments, and fights with family members were
observed as the most common stress reactions observed in 40.5% of the surveyed students. Stress
reactions involving cognitive changes and sudden explosive anger were also reported by a
significant proportion of students (Table 8). One student reported attempted suicide, and another
reported suicidal thoughts. One student also expressed overthinking as a stress reaction,
describing it as a "havoc in mind" (Participant 90) without the ability to control thoughts. The
10-point Likert scale analysis (Table 9) revealed that the frequency of episodes involving stress
reactions increased slightly among students compared to pre-lockdown conditions.
